{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ac8f883e15ef792f8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are a research sub-agent. You have WebSearch and WebFetch tools (load them first via ToolSearch with query \"select:WebSearch,WebFetch\" if needed).\n\nRESEARCH ANGLE: The consensus that every working self-improving AI code system needs a GROUND-TRUTH EVALUATOR / verifier (unit tests, a benchmark, a formal verifier, a compiler, automated metrics) to provide the selection/training signal — without it the loop has no gradient and collapses.\n\nFind specific, quotable statements from:\n- AlphaEvolve (DeepMind, 2025) — they emphasize it only works on problems with automated/machine-gradeable evaluators.\n- Darwin Godel Machine (Sakana AI / Jeff Clune et al., 2025) — uses coding benchmarks (SWE-bench, Polyglot) as the empirical validation signal.\n- STOP: Self-Taught Optimizer (Zelikman et al., 2023) — scaffolding improvement requires a measurable utility/objective function.\n- Commentary/analysis articles articulating \"no verifier = no signal\".\n\nRun 4-6 WebSearch queries. Then WebFetch the 4-6 best primary sources (arxiv abstracts, DeepMind blog, paper PDFs/HTML). Extract the exact wording where possible.\n\nSearch terms to try: \"AlphaEvolve automated evaluation function\", \"AlphaEvolve machine-gradeable\", \"Darwin Godel Machine SWE-bench coding benchmark\", \"Self-Taught Optimizer STOP utility function scaffolding\", \"self-improvement requires verifiable reward\", \"RSI needs ground truth evaluator\".\n\nOUTPUT: Return a list of 5-10 FALSIFIABLE CLAIMS. Each claim must be:\n- A single concrete factual sentence\n- Followed by the EXACT source URL\n- Followed by a short verbatim quote or close paraphrase supporting it\nDo not pad. Only return claims you actually found support for in fetched pages."},"uuid":"e41d27e5-5f2b-4eb1-b1c2-65e3f9d883ef","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:12.594Z","userType":