{"parentUuid":"5fad00ea-58ad-4fdc-9c99-3ed3d685af1a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ac8f883e15ef792f8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Luv71yarz7a5pCFeE263FE","type":"tool_result","content":"# AlphaEvolve's Evaluation Requirements\n\nBased on the webpage content, here are the exact statements about AlphaEvolve's need for automated evaluation:\n\n**On verification and scoring:**\n\"AlphaEvolve verifies, runs and scores the proposed programs using automated evaluation metrics.\"\n\n**On domain applicability:**\n\"This makes AlphaEvolve particularly helpful in a broad range of domains where progress can be clearly and systematically measured, like in math and computer science.\"\n\n**On problem prerequisites:**\n\"it can be applied to any problem whose solution can be described as an algorithm, and automatically verified.\"\n\n---\n\nThe webpage emphasizes that AlphaEvolve depends on **automated evaluation metrics** to assess solutions objectively. It functions best on problems where correctness and quality can be measured systematically through programmatic means, rather than subjective assessment."}]},"uuid":"a21420b9-41f8-4d77-9ff9-a08a99f8dd6f","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:45.508Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":151623,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# AlphaEvolve's Evaluation Requirements\n\nBased on the webpage content, here are the exact statements about AlphaEvolve's need for automated evaluation:\n\n**On verification and scoring:**\n\"AlphaEvolve verifies, runs and scores the proposed programs using automated evaluation metrics.\"\n\n**On domain applicability:**\n\"This makes AlphaEvolve particularly helpful in a broad range of domains where progress can be clearly and systematically measured, like in math and computer science.\"\n\n**On problem prerequisites:**\n\"it can be applied to any problem whose solution can be described as an algorithm, and automatically verified.\"\n\n---\n\nThe webpage emphasizes that AlphaEvolve depends on **automated evaluation metrics** to assess solutions objectively. It functions best on problems where correctness and quality can be measured systematically through programmatic means, rather than subjective assessment.","durationMs":3723,"url":"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5fad00ea-58ad-4fdc-9c99-3ed3d685af1a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"c32f5386-a3ae-4a81-bf2e-5f3c1e072f58","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ac8f883e15ef792f8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011hmYKAZ7raNzJAxMErRQze","type":"tool_result","content":"# Darwin Godel Machine: Performance Improvements\n\nHere are the exact verbatim sentences from the abstract regarding empirical validation and performance metrics:\n\n**On empirical validation method:**\n\"It grows the archive by sampling an agent from it and using a foundation model to create a new, interesting, version of the sampled agent.\"\n\n**On performance improvements:**\n\"Empirically, the DGM automatically improves its coding capabilities (e.g., better code editing tools, long-context window management, peer-review mechanisms), increasing performance on SWE-bench from 20.0% to 50.0%, and on Polyglot from 14.2% to 30.7%.\"\n\nThe abstract indicates the system uses coding benchmarks (SWE-bench and Polyglot) as the fitness signal for validating whether self-modifications are beneficial, with substantial performance gains demonstrated on both benchmarks."}]},"uuid":"21c4159c-d252-47e0-a6e8-20fb4c8a8752","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:47.286Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":48792,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Darwin Godel Machine: Performance Improvements\n\nHere are the exact verbatim sentences from the abstract regarding empirical validation and performance metrics:\n\n**On empirical validation method:**\n\"It grows the archive by sampling an agent from it and using a foundation model to create a new, interesting, version of the sampled agent.\"\n\n**On performance improvements:**\n\"Empirically, the DGM automatically improves its coding capabilities (e.g., better code editing tools, long-context window management, peer-review mechanisms), increasing performance on SWE-bench from 20.0% to 50.0%, and on Polyglot from 14.2% to 30.7%.\"\n\nThe abstract indicates the system uses coding benchmarks (SWE-bench and Polyglot) as the fitness signal for validating whether self-modifications are beneficial, with substantial performance gains demonstrated on both benchmarks.","durationMs":3419,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c32f5386-a3ae-4a81-bf2e-5f3c1e072f58","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"d07f104c-cd08-4d40-bff4-1af33d5ccd81","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ac8f883e15ef792f8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HfWByua9ZP1nqP9J3fwUNR","type":"tool_result","content":"# Utility Function in STOP Abstract\n\nThe abstract contains this relevant passage:\n\n\"We start with a seed 'improver' that improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying an LM several times and returning the best solution.\"\n\nThis is the only explicit mention of the utility function requirement in the provided abstract. The text indicates the improver uses a utility function to guide the improvement process, but the abstract does not elaborate on how downstream tasks relate to this utility function or provide additional details about measuring improvement beyond selecting the best solution from multiple LM-generated candidates."}]},"uuid":"bd617b01-e292-4e56-9df5-424e9b34f600","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:48.272Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":47180,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Utility Function in STOP Abstract\n\nThe abstract contains this relevant passage:\n\n\"We start with a seed 'improver' that improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying an LM several times and returning the best solution.\"\n\nThis is the only explicit mention of the utility function requirement in the provided abstract. The text indicates the improver uses a utility function to guide the improvement process, but the abstract does not elaborate on how downstream tasks relate to this utility function or provide additional details about measuring improvement beyond selecting the best solution from multiple LM-generated candidates.","durationMs":2554,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02304"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d07f104c-cd08-4d40-bff4-1af33d5ccd81","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33