{"parentUuid":"13a57242-7bdf-4fca-9773-08f772805e11","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ac8f883e15ef792f8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HFfQVHdu9fvdSZQvUGQJFs","type":"tool_result","content":"# STOP's Utility-Driven Self-Improvement\n\nHere are verbatim statements about how STOP's improvements are guided by measurable objectives:\n\n**On the utility function directing improvement:**\n\n\"the goal is to find an improver program I that has high expected utility when used on a downstream task\"\n\n\"STOP selects improver based on a downstream utility improvement\"\n\n**On scoring program quality:**\n\n\"returns the best solution according to the utility function\"\n\n\"We then run this seed improver to improve itself\" — with improvements selected by evaluating \"the best solution according to a utility function by querying a language model several times and returning the best solution\"\n\n**On utility as the improvement signal:**\n\n\"It​(u^,It−1,L)\" — showing the meta-utility function u^ drives each iteration of self-improvement\n\n\"the improver program is itself an optimization problem\" — solved by optimizing the meta-utility measure of downstream task performance\n\nThe core mechanism: each iteration applies the improver to itself using a meta-utility that averages performance across downstream tasks, enabling recursive refinement based on measurable improvement signals."}]},"uuid":"1712e3b6-9f2e-4ce4-b533-a26553146801","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:58.489Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":1840157,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# STOP's Utility-Driven Self-Improvement\n\nHere are verbatim statements about how STOP's improvements are guided by measurable objectives:\n\n**On the utility function directing improvement:**\n\n\"the goal is to find an improver program I that has high expected utility when used on a downstream task\"\n\n\"STOP selects improver based on a downstream utility improvement\"\n\n**On scoring program quality:**\n\n\"returns the best solution according to the utility function\"\n\n\"We then run this seed improver to improve itself\" — with improvements selected by evaluating \"the best solution according to a utility function by querying a language model several times and returning the best solution\"\n\n**On utility as the improvement signal:**\n\n\"It​(u^,It−1,L)\" — showing the meta-utility function u^ drives each iteration of self-improvement\n\n\"the improver program is itself an optimization problem\" — solved by optimizing the meta-utility measure of downstream task performance\n\nThe core mechanism: each iteration applies the improver to itself using a meta-utility that averages performance across downstream tasks, enabling recursive refinement based on measurable improvement signals.","durationMs":5029,"url":"https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2310.02304"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"13a57242-7bdf-4fca-9773-08f772805e11","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
