{"parentUuid":"758bf7b6-eb4e-4465-b514-6d399bf02465","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"96f7ce82-27af-4c04-ae02-270c4873a922","agentId":"ac8f883e15ef792f8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hnv6ikoy6YbKrRsXVZdK2Y","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve limitation requires automated evaluator not suitable manual experimentation human judgment\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve | cbarkinozer | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://cbarkinozer.medium.com/alphaevolve-419242a0a4b4\"},{\"title\":\"Google’s AlphaEvolve: The AI agent that reclaimed 0.7% of Google’s compute – and how to copy it | VentureBeat\",\"url\":\"https://venturebeat.com/ai/googles-alphaevolve-the-ai-agent-that-reclaimed-0-7-of-googles-compute-and-how-to-copy-it\"},{\"title\":\"Can AlphaEvolve Change How We Solve Problems? A Look Inside DeepMind’s Latest Breakthrough\",\"url\":\"https://www.aiwire.net/2025/05/27/can-alphaevolve-change-how-we-solve-problems-a-look-inside-deepminds-latest-breakthrough/\"},{\"title\":\"Paper Review: AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery | by Andrew Lukyanenko | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://artgor.medium.com/paper-review-alphaevolve-a-coding-agent-for-scientific-and-algorithmic-discovery-5732a876c2e2\"},{\"title\":\"Paper Review: AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery – Andrey Lukyanenko\",\"url\":\"https://andlukyane.com/blog/paper-review-alphaevolve\"},{\"title\":\"Google DeepMind AlphaEvolve (May 2026): Algorithm Discovery Moves From Lab Demo to Production System | Buildmind AI\",\"url\":\"https://buildmind.ai/blog/google-deepmind-alphaevolve-may-2026-production-algorithm-discovery/\"},{\"title\":\"Mathematical exploration and discovery at scale\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2511.02864\"},{\"title\":\"Evolving Ranking Functions for Canonical Blow-Ups in Positive Characteristic\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.06553\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant information about AlphaEvolve's limitations regarding automated evaluators:\n\nWhile the use of an automated evaluation metric offers AlphaEvolve a key advantage, it is also a limitation—in particular, it puts tasks that require manual experimentation out of our scope. More specifically, the primary limitation is the need for an automated evaluator; problems requiring manual experimentation or \"wet-lab\" feedback are currently out of scope for this specific approach.\n\nThe primary limitation of AlphaEvolve is its reliance on problems where an automated evaluation function can be designed, which makes it well-suited for computational and mathematical sciences but less applicable to domains requiring physical experiments.\n\nIn essence, AlphaEvolve's requirement for automated evaluators makes it unsuitable for domains that depend on manual experimentation, physical testing, or human judgment in the evaluation process.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"2683476f-a297-451e-b5cb-5e4729458a8b","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:23.245Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve limitation requires automated evaluator not suitable manual experimentation human judgment","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_0155gocFKd4fDDzEWsWSUnxw","content":[{"title":"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery","url":"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf"},{"title":"AlphaEvolve | cbarkinozer | Medium","url":"https://cbarkinozer.medium.com/alphaevolve-419242a0a4b4"},{"title":"Google’s AlphaEvolve: